dictionary.title: process

entry.name: ‎altitude‎
entry.description: height in relation to a certain reference point; (general) distance measurement, usually in the vertical or "up" direction, between a reference datum and a point or object. The reference datum also often varies according to the context

entry.name: ‎autumn‎
entry.description: one of the Earth's four temperate seasons, occurring between summer and winter

entry.name: ‎desiccation‎
entry.description: state of extreme dryness, or the process of extreme drying

entry.name: ‎dry season‎
entry.description: yearly period of low rainfall, especially in the tropics

entry.name: ‎kiln-dried wood‎
entry.description: wood which has been dried in a kiln or oven

entry.name: ‎solid-phase microextraction‎
entry.description: solid phase extraction sampling technique that involves the use of a fiber coated with an extracting phase, that can be a liquid or a solid, which extracts different kinds of analytes from different kinds of media, that can be in liquid or gas phase

entry.name: ‎liquid–liquid extraction‎
entry.description: method to separate compounds based on their relative solubilities in two different immiscible liquids, usually water and an organic solvent; extraction of a substance from one liquid into another liquid phase

entry.name: ‎summer‎
entry.description: one of the Earth's four temperate seasons, occurring between spring and autumn

entry.name: ‎vegetative reproduction‎
entry.description: form of asexual reproduction in plants

entry.name: ‎wet season‎
entry.description: yearly period of high rainfall, especially in the tropics

entry.name: ‎winter‎
entry.description: one of the Earth's four temperate seasons, occurring between autumn and spring
